snippet.textDisplay: This is great stuff! Little teasers like this are all that's needed for SQ42. And the updated Vanduul line looks spot on. I think the new cockpit makes them look more eerie. Which is appropriate. The bubble look is likely the look of a pure Vanduul ship untouched by Esperia. It's Blade, Glaive, Scythe, Stinger, in order. (my guess) If you compare the current Blade to the one in the video the only difference is the cockpit. Even most of the lines lead to the same place.  The Mustang and Cutlass shown on the turntable could be nothing more than "older" models in lore, or just heavily modified pirate ships. And the big mining platform that looks like a huge Pioneer was actually shown a year ago at the end of the SQ42 Cinematic Teaser.
snippet.textOriginal: This is great stuff! Little teasers like this are all that's needed for SQ42. And the updated Vanduul line looks spot on. I think the new cockpit makes them look more eerie. (my guess) If you compare the current Blade to the one in the video the only difference is the cockpit. Even most of the lines lead to the same place.  The Mustang and Cutlass shown on the turntable could be nothing more than "older" models in lore, or just heavily modified pirate ships. And the big mining platform that looks like a huge Pioneer was actually shown a year ago at the end of the SQ42 Cinematic Teaser.
